<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="548" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,150,609]" pageId="17" pageNumber="548">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,186,212]" pageId="17" pageNumber="548">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is comparatively smaller-sized species and characterized as follows: frons black in anterior and posterior parts and yellow in central part; postpedicel black; arista pubescent; thorax black with grey dusting; katepisternum (
<figureCitation box="[425,507,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 44–48" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1928,1952]" captionTargetBox="[176,1415,872,1897]" captionTargetId="figure-188@16.[162,1423,858,1902]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 44–48. Microprosopa haemorrhoidalis (Meigen). 44, Katepisternum, left lateral view; 45, Male tibia, left anterior view; 46, Male sternite V, ventral view; 47, Male terminalia, left lateral view; 48, Male terminalia, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921437" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921437/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="548">Fig. 44</figureCitation>
) with a single seta; fore tibia ventrally with a row of short black spines (
<figureCitation box="[1338,1423,258,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 44–48" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1928,1952]" captionTargetBox="[176,1415,872,1897]" captionTargetId="figure-188@16.[162,1423,858,1902]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 44–48. Microprosopa haemorrhoidalis (Meigen). 44, Katepisternum, left lateral view; 45, Male tibia, left anterior view; 46, Male sternite V, ventral view; 47, Male terminalia, left lateral view; 48, Male terminalia, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921437" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921437/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="548">Fig. 45</figureCitation>
); abdominal tergites black and subshiny; legs yellow; posterior lobes on male sternite V tapered apically and curved inward (
<figureCitation box="[245,330,331,358]" captionStart="FIGURES 44–48" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1928,1952]" captionTargetBox="[176,1415,872,1897]" captionTargetId="figure-188@16.[162,1423,858,1902]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 44–48. Microprosopa haemorrhoidalis (Meigen). 44, Katepisternum, left lateral view; 45, Male tibia, left anterior view; 46, Male sternite V, ventral view; 47, Male terminalia, left lateral view; 48, Male terminalia, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921437" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921437/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="548">Fig. 46</figureCitation>
); male surstyli broad, tapering apically in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[956,1052,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 44–48" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1928,1952]" captionTargetBox="[176,1415,872,1897]" captionTargetId="figure-188@16.[162,1423,858,1902]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 44–48. Microprosopa haemorrhoidalis (Meigen). 44, Katepisternum, left lateral view; 45, Male tibia, left anterior view; 46, Male sternite V, ventral view; 47, Male terminalia, left lateral view; 48, Male terminalia, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921437" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921437/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="548">Figs. 47</figureCitation>
); male cerci covered with setulae, apically close to each other (
<figureCitation box="[471,556,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURES 44–48" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1928,1952]" captionTargetBox="[176,1415,872,1897]" captionTargetId="figure-188@16.[162,1423,858,1902]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 44–48. Microprosopa haemorrhoidalis (Meigen). 44, Katepisternum, left lateral view; 45, Male tibia, left anterior view; 46, Male sternite V, ventral view; 47, Male terminalia, left lateral view; 48, Male terminalia, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921437" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921437/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="548">Fig. 48</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,150,609]" box="[199,567,402,429]" pageId="17" pageNumber="548">
