<collectingCountry box="[533,600,475,501]" name="Japan" pageId="17" pageNumber="548">Japan</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="548" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,150,609]" pageId="17" pageNumber="548">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,511,537]" pageId="17" pageNumber="548">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species can be easily distinguished from other known species of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Becker" authorityYear="1894" box="[1158,1316,511,536]" class="Insecta" family="Scathophagidae" genus="Microprosopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="548" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1158,1316,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="548">Microprosopa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having posterior lobes on sternite V which are tapered apically and curved inward, and broad surstyli in posterior view in male.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
